On this Memorial Day, we want to Thank All of our servicemen and servicewomen, current, retired, past, and those who paid the ultimate sacrifice. These men and women have allowed us to live in a country that is protected by the freedoms established in the Constitution of the United States. Some of you we know your names, and many of you we will never know, but All of you will be respected and honored!

Have a Wonderful Memorial Day.

Dr. Youssef Mosallam.

Senior Maggie Gurney
In Maggie's first year running she quickly became a star of our varsity squad in cross country. She continued to make strides her senior year and developed into a strong leader. Her senior year she decided to run track. Training all Winter, Maggie led her team by both word and action and would have been a top distance runner this season. She is a true leader both inside and outside the classroom. Congratulations Maggie!

Coach Voss and Coach Beth

post_text: RMS would like to recognize Dave Anderson, the head custodian at RMS. Dave has opened up and worked in the building everyday since our closing in March. I just wanted you to know that we appreciate you!!
